td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: +percent Meditate skill</span><hr size=1> Bumping this in hopes of an answer to two questions:<br><br>1. Does +% meditate on items increase the upper limit on mediate skill? One would hope so in that the teo +% to meditate items I have seen are no-drop and there is almost no way someone less than level 52 could get one.<br><br>2. Assuming the answer to question 1 is yes, do +% meditate items stack? I am fortunate in that my 56th level wizard has two of these items at this time.  <p><table border="0" width="41%">  <tr>    <td width="15%"><img src="http://www.frontiernet.net/~carverc/val2.png" </td width="60" height="195">    <td width="85%" valign="bottom"><font color="#008000"><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6355">Valcare Goodfellow</a>,</b><br>60th Crusader<br>Officer, Warlords of Wrath Rodcet Nife<b> <br></b></font>    </td>  </tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueliathen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/02 10:34:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: +percent Meditate skill</span><hr size=1> Just rambling some thoughts on it..<br><br>Part of the problem (I think) is that no one knows how these things work yet.  Though its pretty clear they don't atm.  If it adds a % total to our actual meditate skill, then I can see the problem.  Verant stated a while ago (RoK era) that they can adjust what each skill level actually accomplishes.  For example, the jump from 251 to 252 could be a bigger gain than the jump from 240 to 251.<br><br>So in meditation, each skill level determines how much mana we regen per tick.  Now, if there are no levels set up for anything greater than 252, well obviously it won't work.  So perhaps they are going to effect the mana regen AT our current skill level.  For example: (numbers completely made up)<br><br>Skill level 100: mana regen 20/tick<br>With 5% modifier at a skill of 100: mana regen 21/tick<br><br>Skill level 101: mana regen 30/tick<br>With 5% modifier at skill of 101: mana regen of 21.5/tick<br><br><br>If they do it as a modifier to your base skill, then they will be useless to people who have it maxed already, unless they allow them to surpass current level limit restrictions.  In which case they'll need to assign values for meditate skills greater than 252.<br><br>Another issue is with things like evocation, alteration, etc (casting skills).  I believe those values are run through an algorithm to determine fizzles.  Perhaps those ones are significantly easier to set up?  Dunno, just throwing out ideas. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubaedm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baedm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/2/02 5:00:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: +percent Meditate skill</span><hr size=1> This was in &quot;THE FUTURE OF EQ: FROM DALLAS FAN FAIR&quot; posted on February 1st, 2002 (yesterday) on Castersrealm.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Can you explain how the % bonus items work?<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Those items work like this.  They will raise you above the class caps, so if your skill cap for your class is 100 then they can let you exceed that.  They will not however let you exceed the hard cap at 252.  So if you are level 60 and have say 252 in meditate then a bonus item for meditation isn't going to help you regen mana faster.  Not to say the item still won't be useful  to you for its other stats.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Also according to Castersrealm, our meditate skill caps at 252.  I'm pretty sure this is correct, but not 100%.  I haven't looked at my meditate skill in a while. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If that's the case, +Meditate items will do absolutely nothing for Wizards over 50.  I'm not going to spend time working on a Meditate item quest, nor am I going to speak up on a guild raid if one drops.<br><br>IMO, items with +meditate are best suited for those who don't have 252 meditation.  Namely, Hybrids and Casters under 50.  I bet there are some 50+ casters out there without 252 meditate, but they're few in number. <p><A HREF="mailto:baedm@hotmail.com">Baedm</A> - <A HREF="http://pages.infinit.net/adorno">OSW</A> - <A HREF="http://www.berthall.com">Bertoxxulous</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/10/02 10:33:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/jarninface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: +percent Meditate skill</span><hr size=1> Since Meditation caps at 252, a +5% increase to med will do nothing. However, our spell casting skills cap at 235, so evocation, abjuration, alteration, divination and conjuration would be the skill mods you'd want, not med. <p><center><br><EMBED src="http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/jarninsig02.swf" quality=high loop=trueWIDTH=468 HEIGHT=80 TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash"PLUGINSPAGE="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/index.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash"></EMBED></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.showPrevMessage?topicID=9.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.showNextMessage?topicID=9.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.emailToFriend?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.threadControl?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm36.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><